	"keywords": "javascript, Browsers, API, asynchronous programming",
	"description": "Introduction\nqueueMicrotask is a new browser API which can be used to convert your\nsynchronous code into async:\n\nqueueMicrotask(() &#x3D;&gt; {\n    console.log(&#x27;hey i am executed asychronously by queueMicrotask&#x27;);\n});\n\nIt&#x27;s similar to what we were doing using setTimeout:\n\nsetTimeout(() &#x3D;&gt; {\n    console.log(&#x27;hey i am executed asychronously by setTimeout&#x27;);\n}, 0);\n\nSo what&#x27;s the use of queueMicrotask when we already have setTimeout ?\n\n&gt; queueMicrotask adds the function (task) into a queue and each functio",
