	"description": "This question is often asked in interviews to test the candidate&#x27;s approach to\nthinking about code.\n\nProblem Statement\nYou have a string which contains only 0&#x27;s and 1&#x27;s. You need to write a program\nwhich will return the number of 0&#x27;s and 1&#x27;s, and you are not allowed to use a\ncounter variable by any means. \n\nSeems tricky right? \n\nWorry not - it&#x27;s very simple. I am going to teach you how to do it both ways:\n\n * With a counter (the classic approach)\n * Without using a counter (as required in the in",
